30/01/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Teachers at 1,077 of Serbia's 1,804 schools went on strike Friday (January 28th) demanding a 24.5% hike in their salaries.
The education ministry says the protest is illegal.
It has warned teachers who fail to report to work that they could face reprimands and even termination.
(Reuters, Bloomberg, B92, Tanjug - 28/01/11)
